TWEAK_X11API_PLUGIN_WATCHDOG_TIMEOUT		arjanl
	When a plugin is not responding, that is, it doesn't return control to the
	main loop, a watchdog timer is responsible for killing it off. This setting
	decides how long we allow a plugin to be busy before killing it off.

	The setting is the number of seconds we should wait.

	Value: 15
	Define: X11API_PLUGIN_WATCHDOG_TIMEOUT
	Category: setting
	Depends on: API_X11API
	Disabled for: desktop, mini, minimal, smartphone, tv
